headline: How the rise of dupes and store brands could change the way you shop
summary: Adrianna Rinaldi has enough high-quality leggings to last a week of remote work in New York without having to do laundry - and it didn’t cost her a small fortune. Instead of continuing to spend up to $118 for one pair from Lululemon, she now buys a version that is a third of the price.
